commitResults.messageTitle: Reflect change in todo list in text file
commitResults.messageBody:
Text file does not reflect change in internal list of todo tasks.

If the change is not reflected, progress is not correctly saved
across instances.

Add some file modifying methods to facilitate functionalities such
as:
1. Add Task
2. Delete Task (given index n)

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement Date functionality into Deadline and Event
commitResults.messageBody:
Dates are just strings.

So, users could input deadlines that made no sense (i.e I have a
homework deadline by apple).

Restrict date format to yyyy-mm-dd to not only facilitate logical
dates in the list, but to open up to future date comparison features
as well.

commitResults.messageTitle: Separate methods into different classes based on functionality
commitResults.messageBody:
Everything is in one class (except tasks which was done before)

Divide methods into classes based on their usage (i.e Storage
methods goes to Storage class, etc)

Code is more modular and clean this way

Some status messages show extra indent and line.

User experience would be improved with consistent formatting

commitResults.messageTitle: Package classes based on their uses
commitResults.messageBody:
All classes are in the same directory.

Looks very disorganized. Separating them into different packages
improves project structure.

Move everything into a Lamball Package, then moved tasks into Tasks
package.

commitResults.messageTitle: Package classes based on their uses part 2
commitResults.messageBody:
Classes in original directory not there anymore (moved into package)

Reflect change in directory and build.gradle

Parse function did more than parsing

It is doing other classes' job for them, which makes for non-elegant
code

Clean up parse and move it's extra functionalities to where they
should belong

L in Lamball capitalized in directory

Gradle has issues picking up JUnit tests

Reformat directories, changed Lamball to lamball (directory)
Create some sanity tests to verify gradle file configured properly

Text Comparison is used in testing.

Text comparison between actual and expected does not test for things
like exceptions thrown

Use JUnit to test for non-trivial scenarios like exceptions thrown.

.jar file is named duke for a chatbot named Lamball

Misleading executable file name

Change shadowJar parameters to match chatbot name

No documentation provided for methods.

Add descriptive JavaDoc documentation to better explain the code.

Providing JavaDoc documentation for public methods improves
readability and understandability of code when read by external
parties.

commitResults.messageTitle: Tweak code to comply with coding standard
commitResults.messageBody:
Inconsistent coding standard used in code.

Desire to follow a standardized coding standard so that the code is
more readable.

Added some line breaks and adjusted certain variable naming to suit
the standard coding convention that was required.

commitResults.messageTitle: Tweak code to comply with coding standard p2
commitResults.messageBody:
Deadline class still had methods that did not follow coding standard

Reflects on lack of due diligence if coding standard is found to not
be followed in numerous instances

Fix line break to separate method signatures.

This makes the Deadline class follow the coding standard set.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add find function in chatbot commands
commitResults.messageBody:
Users are unable to search their todo lists with keywords or
markers.

This is bad user design, and especially when more tasks are added
to the todo list, a search function is a necessary feature for users
to filter.

Let's
*Add a 'find' function that is parsable by the parse.
*Update tasklist and other functions to faciliate integration of
said function.

Header descriptions not present.

Bad for other readers and code reviewers because they would require
more time to understand the code and how each part functions
separately.

Add a small javadoc description for every class.

commitResults.messageTitle: Move additional String printing related methods to UI
commitResults.messageBody:
Printlist is printed in TaskList.

Bad because in the structure, Ui is supposed to be doing the Ui
work, and not TaskList.

Streamline all task commands to better allow Ui to do the UI
operations.
